quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  35,19,Not alike are the blind and the seeing
  35,20,Neither darknesses and light
  35,21,Nor the shade and the sun's heat
  35,22,Nor alike are the living and the dead. Verily Allah maketh whomsoever He listeth to hear and thou canst not make them hear who are in the graves
  35,23,Thou art naught but a warner
  35,24,"Verily We! We have sent thee with the truth, as a bearer of glad tidings and as a warner; and there is not a community but there hath passed among them a warner"
  35,25,"And if they belie thee, then surely those before them have also belied. Their apostles came Unto them with evidences and scriptures and a Book luminous"
  35,26,Then I took hold of those who disbelieved. So how terrible was My disapproval
  35,27,"Beholdest thou not that Allah sendeth down water from the heaven, and then We thereby bring fruit of diverse colours? And in the mountains are steaks white and red, of diverse colours, and also intensely black"
  35,28,"And of men and beasts and cattle, likewise of diverse colours. Those only of His bondmen who have knowledge fear Allah Verily Allahis the Mighty, the Forgiving"
  35,29,"Verily those Who read the book of Allah and establish prayer and expend of that wherewith We have provided them, secretly and in open, hope for a merchandise that shall not perish"
  35,30,"That He may pay them their hires in full and increase Unto them of His grace; verily, He is Forgiving, Appreciative"